                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17210525-7-off39 t17210525-7-cd40"></join>. Mr. Biggs deposed that M. Petit lodg'd in his House formerly, but was gone into the Country, having left his Goods in his Custody: that Mr. Petit sent his two Nephews up for his Goods, who told him, that there was a Silver Tankard and Cup wanting, whereupon he took up the Journeyman; who telling him that he had observed the Prisoner (his <rs id="t17210525-7-deflabel41" type="occupation">Apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17210525-7-defend61 t17210525-7-deflabel41"></join>) full of Money, etc. they detected him. 
               <persName id="t17210525-7-person66">
                  Thomas 
                  Davis 
               <interp inst="t17210525-7-person66" type="surname" value="Davis"></interp>
